    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 features the M96 3.4L flat-six, delivering linear power through a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. It has been mechanically sorted with a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The suspension retains its factory-spec geometry with refreshed bushings, ensuring the communicative feedback inherent to its hydraulic steering rack. Equipped with four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors, the braking system provides consistent thermal management. While the exterior shows honest patina, the drivetrain remains robust and responsive.",
